		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In other words, it appears to update the VRAM address on the cycle that the attribute data comes back. Remember that the <span class="posthilit">PPU</span> has a multiplexed bus to reduce pin count, so a read consists of sending out an address and then getting the data back on the next cycle. As I understand it, each 8 cycles during BG rendering look like this:
<br />
<br />0: request nametable byte
<br />1: get nametable byte
<br />2: request attribute table byte
<br />3: get attribute table byte <strong>and update nametable pointer</strong>
<br />4: request pattern bitplane 0
<br />5: get pattern bitplane 0
<br />6: request pattern bitplane 1
<br />7: get pattern bitplane 1

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


